@echo off

rem #  INIT THE TOKEN BUILDER VARIABLES
set cyear=
set cdate=
set chours=
set ctime=

rem #  ASSIGN THE BASIC INFOS WE GOT FROM THE STARTUP CALL
set VmId=%1%
set VMSInstallPath=%cd%

goto START


rem #  SETUP SOME HELPER METHODS AND JUMPPOINTS
:WAIT_FOR_SHUTDOWN
\%VMSInstallPath%\tools\sleep.exe" 3
echo Waiting for a previous shutdown of VM%VmId% to complete...
goto START


rem #  ACTUAL SCRIPT PROCESSING STARTS HERE
:START

rem #  CHECK FOR THE BRUTEFORCE OPTION
if "%2%" == "BRUTEFORCE" goto BRUTEFORCE
goto NOBRUTEFORCE


:BRUTEFORCE
rem #  KILL ANY POSSIBLY EXISTING RUNFILES AND/OR LOCKFILES BEFORE STARTUP
echo BRUTEFORCE: Killing all existing run- / lockfiles for this VM...
if exist "%VMSInstallPath%\run\*.vm%VmId%" echo killing: "%VMSInstallPath%\run\*.vm%VmId%"
if exist "%VMSInstallPath%\run\*.vm%VmId%" del "%VMSInstallPath%\run\*.vm%VmId%"

if exist "%VMSInstallPath%\lock\*.UP.vm%VmId%" echo killing: "%VMSInstallPath%\lock\*.UP.vm%VmId%"
if exist "%VMSInstallPath%\lock\*.UP.vm%VmId%" del "%VMSInstallPath%\lock\*.UP.vm%VmId%"

if exist "%VMSInstallPath%\lock\*.DOWN.vm%VmId%" echo killing: "%VMSInstallPath%\lock\*.DOWN.vm%VmId%"
if exist "%VMSInstallPath%\lock\*.DOWN.vm%VmId%" del "%VMSInstallPath%\lock\*.DOWN.vm%VmId%"

if exist "%VMSInstallPath%\lock\runserv.lock" echo killing: "%VMSInstallPath%\lock\runserv.lock"
if exist "%VMSInstallPath%\lock\runserv.lock" del "%VMSInstallPath%\lock\runserv.lock"
goto SKIPCHECK


:NOBRUTEFORCE
rem #  CHECK FOR A LOCKFILE SET BY A PREVIOUSLY TRIGGERED SHUTDOWN CALL TO THIS VM
if exist "%VMSInstallPath%\run\*.vm%VmId%" goto ABORT_ALREADY_RUNNING
if exist "%VMSInstallPath%\lock\*.UP.vm%VmId%" goto ABORT_ALREADY_RUNNING_STARTUP
if exist "%VMSInstallPath%\lock\*.DOWN.vm%VmId%" goto WAIT_FOR_SHUTDOWN

:SKIPCHECK

FOR /F "tokens=1

set PathToVBoxVRDP=
set PathToVBoxManage=
set RunAsUser=
set RunAtDomain=
set UserPassword=
set VmName=

set ShutdownMethod=

rem #  POPULATING ALL VARIABLES

"%VMSInstallPath%\tools\inifile.exe" VBoxVmService.ini [Settings] > "%VMSInstallPath%\tmp\u_%VmId%_globals.bat"
call "%VMSInstallPath%\tmp\u_%VmId%_globals.bat"
del "%VMSInstallPath%\tmp\u_%VmId%_globals.bat"

echo Reading parameters for VM%VmId%...
"%VMSInstallPath%\tools\inifile.exe" VBoxVmService.ini [Vm%VmId%] > "%VMSInstallPath%\tmp\u_%VmId%_vmvals.bat"
call "%VMSInstallPath%\tmp\u_%VmId%_vmvals.bat"
del "%VMSInstallPath%\tmp\u_%VmId%_vmvals.bat"

rem #  VALIDATE THE OBTAINED VALUES
if "%VmName%" == "" goto NORUN
if "%RunAsUser%" == "" goto NORUN
if "%RunAtDomain%" == "" goto NORUN
if "%UserPassword%" == "" goto NORUN
if "%StartupMethod%" == "" goto NORUN
if "%ShutdownMethod%" == "" goto NORUN


rem #  DECIDING WHICH STARTUP METHOD TO USE
if "%StartupMethod%" == "sdl" goto STARTUP_SDL
if "%StartupMethod%" == "SDL" goto STARTUP_SDL
if "%StartupMethod%" == "vrdp" goto STARTUP_VRDP
if "%StartupMethod%" == "VRDP" goto STARTUP_VRDP
goto NORUN

rem #  GENERATING THE TEMPORARY HELPFILES
echo Generating temporary helpfiles...

:STARTUP_SDL
if "%PathToVBoxSDL%" == "" goto NORUN
echo "%PathToVBoxSDL%" -vm "%VmName%" > "%VMSInstallPath%\tmp\u_%VmId%_sub.bat"
"%VMSInstallPath%\tools\bcompile.exe" "%VMSInstallPath%\tmp\u_%VmId%_sub.bat" "%VMSInstallPath%\tmp\u_%VmId%_sub.exe" -hidden 
del "%VMSInstallPath%\tmp\u_%VmId%_sub.bat"
goto MAKE_RUNFILE

:STARTUP_VRDP
if "%PathToVBoxVRDP%" == "" goto NORUN
if "%VrdpPort%" == "" goto STARTUP_VRDP_DEFAULTPORT
if "%VrdpPort%" == "0" goto STARTUP_VRDP_DEFAULTPORT
if "%VrdpPort%" == "3389" goto STARTUP_VRDP_DEFAULTPORT

echo Using custom VRDP-Port: %VrdpPort%
echo "%PathToVBoxManage%" modifyvm "%VmName%" -vrdpport %VrdpPort% > "%VMSInstallPath%\tmp\u_%VmId%_vrdpset.bat"
goto STARTUP_VRDP_STEP_2

:STARTUP_VRDP_DEFAULTPORT
echo Using default VRDP-Port: 3389
echo "%PathToVBoxManage%" modifyvm "%VmName%" -vrdpport 3389 > "%VMSInstallPath%\tmp\u_%VmId%_vrdpset.bat"

:STARTUP_VRDP_STEP_2
call "%VMSInstallPath%\tmp\u_%VmId%_vrdpset.bat" >NUL

echo "%PathToVBoxVRDP%" -startvm "%VmName%" > "%VMSInstallPath%\tmp\u_%VmId%_sub.bat"
"%VMSInstallPath%\tools\bcompile.exe" "%VMSInstallPath%\tmp\u_%VmId%_sub.bat" "%VMSInstallPath%\tmp\u_%VmId%_sub.exe" -hidden 
del "%VMSInstallPath%\tmp\u_%VmId%_sub.bat"

:MAKE_RUNFILE
echo "%VMSInstallPath%\tools\runasv.exe" "%VMSInstallPath%\tmp\u_%VmId%_sub.exe" \%RunAtDomain%\%RunAsUser% "%UserPassword%" > "%VMSInstallPath%\tmp\u_%VmId%_run.bat"
"%VMSInstallPath%\tools\bcompile.exe" "%VMSInstallPath%\tmp\u_%VmId%_run.bat" "%VMSInstallPath%\tmp\u_%VmId%_run.exe" -hidden 
del "%VMSInstallPath%\tmp\u_%VmId%_run.bat"
set UserPassword=

rem #  Delete the VRDP-Postsetup helper file
del "%VMSInstallPath%\tmp\u_%VmId%_vrdpset.bat"

rem #  CHECK FOR AN ACTIVE RUNSERV PROCESS
if exist "%VMSInstallPath%\lock\runserv.lock" goto SKIP_START_RUNSERV


rem #  NO RUNSERV? SO LET'S BRING IT UP!
echo 1 > "%VMSInstallPath%\lock\runserv.lock"
echo Installing temporary service "runserv"...
"%VMSInstallPath%\tools\runserv.exe" -c
"%VMSInstallPath%\tools\sleep.exe" 2

echo Shutting down "runserv" to avoid malfunctions...
"%VMSInstallPath%\VBoxVmService.exe" -k runserv
"%VMSInstallPath%\tools\sleep.exe" 3

echo Restarting "runserv"...
"%VMSInstallPath%\VBoxVmService.exe" -r runserv
"%VMSInstallPath%\tools\sleep.exe" 4

:SKIP_START_RUNSERV


rem # NOW CALL THE ACTUAL STARTUP COMMANDS
echo Starting VM: "%VmName%" via %StartupMethod% as a service using account: "%RunAsUser%"...
"%VMSInstallPath%\tmp\u_%VmId%_run.exe" 
"%VMSInstallPath%\tools\sleep.exe" 15
goto MARK_RUNNING

:NORUN
echo Errors occurred trying to start VM%VmId%! 
echo Check the VBoxVmServ.ini values

if "%StartupMethod%" == "" goto NORUN
if "%ShutdownMethod%" == "" goto NORUN

rem #  GENERATING THE TEMPORARY HELPFILES
echo Generating temporary helpfiles... >> "%VMSInstallPath%\VBoxVmService.log"
echo "%PathToVBoxManage%" controlvm "%VmName%" "%ShutdownMethod%" > "%VMSInstallPath%\tmp\d_%VmId%_sub.bat"
"%VMSInstallPath%\tools\bcompile.exe" "%VMSInstallPath%\tmp\d_%VmId%_sub.bat" "%VMSInstallPath%\tmp\d_%VmId%_sub.exe" -hidden 
del "%VMSInstallPath%\tmp\d_%VmId%_sub.bat"

echo "%VMSInstallPath%\tools\runasv.exe" "%VMSInstallPath%\tmp\d_%VmId%_sub.exe" \%RunAtDomain%\%RunAsUser% "%UserPassword%" > "%VMSInstallPath%\tmp\d_%VmId%_run.bat"
"%VMSInstallPath%\tools\bcompile.exe" "%VMSInstallPath%\tmp\d_%VmId%_run.bat" "%VMSInstallPath%\tmp\d_%VmId%_run.exe" -hidden 
del "%VMSInstallPath%\tmp\d_%VmId%_run.bat"
set UserPassword=


rem #  CHECK FOR AN ACTIVE RUNSERV PROCESS
if exist "%VMSInstallPath%\lock\runserv.lock" goto SKIP_START_RUNSERV


rem #  NO RUNSERV? SO LET'S BRING IT UP!
echo 1 > "%VMSInstallPath%\lock\runserv.lock"
echo Installing temporary service "runserv"... >> "%VMSInstallPath%\VBoxVmService.log"
"%VMSInstallPath%\tools\runserv.exe" -c
"%VMSInstallPath%\tools\sleep.exe" 2

echo Shutting down "runserv" to avoid malfunctions... >> "%VMSInstallPath%\VBoxVmService.log"
"%VMSInstallPath%\VBoxVmService.exe" -k runserv
"%VMSInstallPath%\tools\sleep.exe" 3

echo Restarting "runserv"...
"%VMSInstallPath%\VBoxVmService.exe" -r runserv
"%VMSInstallPath%\tools\sleep.exe" 4

:SKIP_START_RUNSERV


rem # NOW CALL THE ACTUAL SHUTDOWN COMMANDS
echo Shutting down serviced VM: "%VmName%" with option %ShutdownMethod% running on account: "%RunAsUser%"... >> "%VMSInstallPath%\VBoxVmService.log"
"%VMSInstallPath%\tmp\d_%VmId%_run.exe" 
"%VMSInstallPath%\tools\sleep.exe" 15
goto MARK_SHUTDOWN

:NORUN
echo Errors occurred trying to shut down VM%VmId%! >> "%VMSInstallPath%\VBoxVmService.log"
echo Check the VBoxVmServ.ini values
column4545:
sections [Settings] and [Vm%VmId%]!
set NoRun=%VmId%
goto CHECK_RUNSERV


:MARK_SHUTDOWN
rem # REMOVE THE RUN LOCKFILE
del "%VMSInstallPath%\run\*.vm%VmId%"
echo Removing lockfile: RUN  >> "%VMSInstallPath%\VBoxVmService.log"


:CHECK_RUNSERV
rem # REMOVE THE SHUTDOWN LOCKFILE
del "%VMSInstallPath%\lock\%tokenid%.DOWN.vm%VmId%"
echo Removing lockfile: SHUTDOWN >> "%VMSInstallPath%\VBoxVmService.log"


rem # CHECK WHETHER RUNSERV IS CURRENTLY NEEDED BY OTHERS
dir /b /o:n "%VMSInstallPath%\lock\" > "%VMSInstallPath%\tmp\vm%VmId%down.chk"
set /P removerunserv=<"%VMSInstallPath%\tmp\vm%VmId%down.chk"
if "%removerunserv%"=="runserv.lock" goto SHUTDOWN_RUNSERV

goto CLEANUP


rem # SHUT RUNSERV DOWN IF IT IS NOT NEEDED BY OTHERS
:SHUTDOWN_RUNSERV 

del "%VMSInstallPath%\lock\runserv.lock"

echo Shutting down "runserv"... >> "%VMSInstallPath%\VBoxVmService.log"
"%VMSInstallPath%\VBoxVmService.exe" -k runserv
"%VMSInstallPath%\tools\sleep.exe" 1

echo Removing temporary service "runserv"... >> "%VMSInstallPath%\VBoxVmService.log"
"%VMSInstallPath%\tools\runserv.exe" -b


rem # DO SOME FINAL CLEANUP ON FILES
:CLEANUP

echo Removing temporary helpfiles... >> "%VMSInstallPath%\VBoxVmService.log"
if "%NoRun%" == "%VmId%" goto SKIP_EXE
del "%VMSInstallPath%\tmp\d_%VmId%_sub.exe"
del "%VMSInstallPath%\tmp\d_%VmId%_run.exe"

:SKIP_EXE
del "%VMSInstallPath%\tmp\vm%VmId%down.chk"

rem # AND ON THE VARIABLES 
set PathToVBoxSDL=
set PathToVBoxVRDP=
set PathToVBoxManage=
set RunAsUser=
set RunAtDomain=
set UserPassword=
set StartupMethod=
set ShutdownMethod=
set VmName=
set VmId=
set NoRun=
set VMSInstallPath=

goto DONE


:ABORT_NOT_RUNNING
echo This VM does not seem to be currently running. Shutdown call aborted. >> "%VMSInstallPath%\VBoxVmService.log"
goto END


:ABORT_ALREADY_RUNNING_SHUTDOWN
echo This VM seems to be currently in shutdown. Additional shutdown call aborted. >> "%VMSInstallPath%\VBoxVmService.log"
goto END


:DONE


:ENDBSJB"
